def_model <- function(hp) {
  
  # define sequential model
  model <- keras::keras_model_sequential()
  
  # Choose the number of hidden layers using the `Int` hyperparameter
  hp_num_layers <- hp$Int('num_layers', min_value = 1, max_value = 3, step = 1)
  
  
  for(i in 1:hp_num_layers){
    model %>%
      layer_dense(units = hp$Int("units", min_value = 8, max_value = 64, step = 8), input_shape = ncol(train_input)) %>%
      layer_batch_normalization() %>%
      {
        activation_function <- hp$Choice("activation", values = c("linear", "relu", "leaky_relu"))
        # activation_function <- hp$Choice("activation", values = c("relu"))
        
        if (activation_function == "relu") {
          . %>% layer_activation_relu()
        } else if (activation_function == "leaky_relu") {
          . %>% layer_activation_leaky_relu(alpha = hp$Float("alpha", min_value = 0.01, max_value = 0.3, sampling = "log"))
        } else {
          . %>% layer_activation(activation = 'linear')
        }
      } %>%
      {
        # Ensure dropout is a valid number and within the appropriate range.
        dropout_rate <- hp$Float("dropout", min_value = 0, max_value = 0.2, step = 0.05)
        
        if (is.finite(dropout_rate) && dropout_rate >= 0 && dropout_rate <= 1) {
          . %>% layer_dropout(rate = dropout_rate)
        } else {
          stop("Invalid dropout rate: ", dropout_rate)
        }
      }
    
  } 
  
  model %>%
    layer_dense(units = ncol(train_response), activation = 'linear')  # Regression task with linear activation
  
  model %>% compile(
    optimizer = optimizer_adam(learning_rate = hp$Float("learning_rate", min_value = 0.0001, max_value = 0.01, sampling='log')),
    loss = 'mse',
    metrics ='mse'
  )
  
  return(model)
}

best_model = tuner %>% kerastuneR::get_best_models(num_models=1)

predicted = best_model[[1]] %>% predict(train_input)
## 6/6 - 0s - 5ms/step
model_keras = best_model[[1]]


# == predict in validation data
valid_predicted = best_model[[1]] %>% predict(valid_pca)
## 3/3 - 0s - 3ms/step
# == evaluate predicted vs. observed values
valid_cors = lapply(1:ncol(valid_predicted), function(x) broom::tidy(cor.test(valid_predicted[,x], valid_response[,x])))
names(valid_cors) = colnames(valid_response)
valid_cors_df = ldply(valid_cors, .id='gene')
valid_cors_df = valid_cors_df[order(valid_cors_df$estimate, decreasing = T), ]
valid_cors_df$fdr = p.adjust(valid_cors_df$p.value, 'fdr')
valid_cors_df$bonf = p.adjust(valid_cors_df$p.value, 'bonferroni')

# - plot the distribution of prediction accuracies for SynGO transcripts
ggplot(valid_cors_df, aes(x = estimate)) +
  geom_density() +
  theme_classic() +
  xlab("Prediction Pearson's r") +
  ylab("Density") +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size=11, color='black'),
        axis.title = element_text(size=11))

# plot of predicted vs. observed for top gene
top_gene = valid_cors_df$gene[1]
top_gene_index = which(colnames(valid_response) %in% top_gene)

qplot(y = valid_response[,top_gene_index],  x = valid_predicted[,top_gene_index]) +
  geom_point(col='darkorange') +
  geom_smooth(method='lm') +
  theme_classic() +
  stat_cor(col='black', size=5) +
  labs(title = top_gene) +
  xlab("Predicted expression") +
  ylab("Observed expression") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(face=3),
        axis.text = element_text(color='black', size=10.5))

## 3/3 - 0s - 4ms/step
# plot(shap) # <-- standard plot (optional)

shap_avg = ddply(shap, .(variable_name), summarize, mean = mean(contribution), se = sd(contribution)/sqrt(length(contribution)))
shap_avg$lwr = shap_avg$mean - (1.96 * shap_avg$se)
shap_avg$upr = shap_avg$mean + (1.96 * shap_avg$se)
shap_avg$zero_overlap = ifelse(shap_avg$lwr <= 0 & shap_avg$upr >= 0, "overlap", "nooverlap")
plot_shap_avg = shap_avg[shap_avg$zero_overlap %in% "nooverlap",]

ggplot(plot_shap_avg, aes(x = reorder(variable_name, -mean), y = mean)) +
  geom_bar(stat='identity', col='black', lwd=0.2, fill=ifelse(plot_shap_avg$mean < 0, "salmon","dodgerblue4")) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), width=0.2, lwd=0.2) +
  theme_bw() +
  xlab("Variable") +
  ylab("Normalized Prediction Contribution") +
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(),
        axis.text = element_text(size=8.11, color='black'),
        axis.text.x = element_text(hjust=1, angle=45))

# feature loadings for pca
plot_shap_avg = plot_shap_avg[order(abs(plot_shap_avg$mean), decreasing = T), ]
ranked_loadings = loadings[,plot_shap_avg$variable_name[1:5]]

ranked = apply(ranked_loadings, 2, function(x) abs(x) >= quantile(abs(x), .9999))
ranked = ranked_loadings[rownames(ranked_loadings) %in% names(which(rowSums(ranked) > 0)),]

gtf = fread("~/Documents/bin/BrainGENIE/gtf/gencode.v39.GRCh38.genes.gtf")
gtf = gtf[,c("gene_name","gene_id")]
gtf$gene_name_fix = gsub("[-]", ".", gtf$gene_name)
gtf = gtf[gtf$gene_name_fix %in% rownames(ranked), ]
gtf = gtf[match(rownames(ranked), gtf$gene_name_fix), ]
rownames(ranked) = gtf$gene_name

# plot top driving genes
melted = reshape2::melt(ranked)

ggplot(melted, aes(x = reorder(Var2, -value), y = reorder(Var1, -value), fill = value)) +
  geom_tile() +
  coord_equal() + 
  xlab("Top contributing PCs") +
  ylab("Driving genes") +
  scale_fill_gradient2("PC loading", low = 'coral1', mid = 'white', midpoint = 0, high = 'cyan') +
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_text(hjust=1, angle=45),
        axis.text.y = element_text(face=3),
        axis.text = element_text(size=11, color='black'))
